  "blocks": [
    {
      "id": "steel_structure",
      "type": "text",
      "label": "钢结构设计与细化",
      "content": "**Steel Structure**: 设计用于自动化立体仓库货架的钢结构。\n**Detailed Design**: 对立体仓库货架的钢结构设计进行细化。\nRefined Structure: Detailed dimensions and specifications for each component of the立体仓库货架.\nMaterial Breakdown: List of materials required, including steel types, sizes, and quantities for production.",
      "children": [],
      "x": 100,
      "y": 80,
      "width": 210.41661537215654,
      "height": 289
    },
    {
      "id": "order_processing",
      "type": "text",
      "label": "Order Processing",
      "content": "Steps to place orders with suppliers based on the material breakdown.",
      "children": [],
      "x": 255.20830768607829,
      "y": 409,
      "width": 200,
      "height": 122
    },
    {
      "id": "bolt_calculation",
      "type": "text",
      "label": "螺栓计算与管理",
      "content": "Bolt Calculation: Column bolts rely on base and connection plates. Check tensile and shear strength. Beam bolts follow beam design parameters. Distinguish between friction and bearing connections. Diagonal braces and washers follow a fixed ratio. Formula: (Brace×2 + Washer×1)/2. Result equals one brace per half washer set. Example: Ten braces need five washer sets.\nVBA Automation: VBA scripts handle automatic counting. Format tables and export BOM lists instantly. Cut manual workload and prevent counting errors.\nRule Table: Links material names to calculation logic. Uses ID prefixes for automatic matching. Supports wildcard queries. Example: ID starting with \"B-\" applies beam bolt standards.\nBolt Surplus: Surplus calculation lacks fixed rules. Recommend adding a standard loss factor of 3% to 5%. Clarify spare parts for on-site adjustments. Standardize parameters before automation.",
      "children": [],
      "x": 1035.2083076860783,
      "y": 409,
      "width": 200,
      "height": 754
    },
